cmd:node hello.js 
============================================
NPM - Node package manager
cmd:npm -v
npm version should be greater then 5.6
//It helps to manage the packages in our project
=====================================
npm:
package.json file
cmd:npm init
//It is configuration file
//It consists of information about the project and set of packages installed and how to run the project.

Using npm how to start the project
1.inside the scripts tag please create key and value pair
2.inside the key please provide any name with small case character
3.value should command to execute that code:
  "scripts": {
    "start":"node index.js"
  },
cmd:npm run start
cmd:npm start
===================
0.27.2
0 - major version 
27 - minor version
2 - patch version
0.28.3 - you can update
1.01.0 - testing is needed
^symbol will update minor and patch version
========================
//any package you are going to install will be store in node_modules folder
//Inside then node_modules folder we cannot do anything because it will install everything from network or cloud 
//package.lock.json  this file will be created automatically whenever we install the new package.
==============================
npm install - will install all the packages that is available inside the package.json->dependencies
===============================
